wifi: mt76: mt7925: add STA fallback recovery in TX free path

mt7925_txwi_free lacks the STA fallback recovery that
mt76_connac2_txwi_free (mt7921) has. When firmware sends MSDU entries
without a preceding WCID pair entry, sta stays NULL and
mt7925_tx_check_aggr never runs, preventing AMPDU BA session setup.

Add the same fallback pattern: re-read WCID from TXD1, look up the
STA via __mt76_wcid_ptr, and call tx_check_aggr if found. Also add
debug tracing in both mt7925_txwi_free (fallback path) and
mt7925_mac_tx_free (PAIR lookup failure) to diagnose whether firmware
reports correct WCIDs for AP-mode client STAs.

Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
Tested-by: Patryk Kowalczyk <patryk@kowalczyk.ws>

7b507603b9e2cf8db74b9164453229decdd927a6
diff --git a/mt7925/mac.c b/mt7925/mac.c
index 4d272f0..eb09e74 100644
--- a/mt7925/mac.c
+++ b/mt7925/mac.c
@@ -1089,2 +1089,13 @@ void mt7925_txwi_free(struct mt792x_dev *dev, struct mt76_txwi_cache *t,
 		wcid_idx = le32_get_bits(txwi[1], MT_TXD1_WLAN_IDX);
+		wcid = __mt76_wcid_ptr(mdev, wcid_idx);
+
+		if (wcid && wcid->sta) {
+			sta = container_of((void *)wcid,
+					   struct ieee80211_sta,
+					   drv_priv);
+			pr_info_ratelimited("mt7925 txwi_free: fallback sta=%pM wcid_idx=%u\n",
+					    sta->addr, wcid_idx);
+			if (likely(t->skb->protocol != cpu_to_be16(ETH_P_PAE)))
+				mt7925_tx_check_aggr(sta, t->skb, wcid);
+		}
 	}
@@ -1137,4 +1148,7 @@ mt7925_mac_tx_free(struct mt792x_dev *dev, void *data, int len)
 			sta = wcid_to_sta(wcid);
-			if (!sta)
+			if (!sta) {
+				pr_info_ratelimited("mt7925 txfree: wcid_idx=%u sta=NULL wcid_sta=%d\n",
+						    idx, wcid ? wcid->sta : -1);
 				continue;
+			}
 
